events.name: Firebase Study Jams
events.description: Come out to Sonoma County for a Firebase study Jam! All are welcome, please bring your PC's to run this program on. We will be building a web app from scratch with Firebase and Stackblitz's online editor. We'll be using basic HTML and JavaScript to talk to Firebase. This is a great intro to using the Firebase console and integrating Firebase into an app. No extensive prior knowledge or software installations needed. This study jam will be broken up into a few meetups to ensure all information is clear and the goal will be met. This meeting we will be getting started downloading the programs and walking through it and the next meeting we will pick up where we left off.

events.name: Firebase Study Jams
events.description: Sign on to zoom from home and join us in another Firebase study jam! All are welcome.. We will be building a web app from scratch with Firebase and Stackblitz's online editor. We'll be using basic HTML and JavaScript to talk to Firebase. This is a great intro to using the Firebase console and integrating Firebase into an app. No extensive prior knowledge or software installations needed. This study jam will be the second part of the Firebase study jam meetings. This meeting we will be doing the study jam thoroughly.

WEB DEVELOPMENT AMP COURSE! Every Mobile App and Website needs to be working efficiently and properly One SUPER FAST and efficient way is AMP! On Friday May 8th we will show the benefits on how to make websites using AMP! Come talk tech, learn and grow! This is a great way to use this quarantine as a way to reach new levels and grow!

Join the video meeting on Zoom:

Time: May 8,[masked]:00 PM Pacific Time (US and Canada)

Join Zoom Meeting

You will be able to get hands-on experience with AMP and build an AMP website while learning the web fundamentals. We recommend that you follow the code with the online editor Glitch. I will give the course link as well as any other link you may need to complete this course during the meeting.

Your own PC, Mac or Chromebook with a good internet connection and access to zoom.
